title: Re: ‘Hollywood, don’t divide us’: Trump supporters gather at Hollywood and Vine
text:
‘Hollywood, don’t divide us’: Trump supporters gather at Hollywood and Vine Posted at 5:25 pm on February 26, 2017 by William A. 
The Oscars are tonight and many expect those inside to target President Trump. 
But this gathering is taking place at Hollywood and Vine at the Metro station: This is the complete group of #Trump supporters gathered outside the Hollywood/Vine station pic.twitter.com/2mr0hUjeOU 
— Brittny Mejia (@brittny_mejia) February 26, 2017 #Trump supporters are gathered outside the Metro station near Hollywood and Vine. pic.twitter.com/P6Bgs8SDD5 
— Brittny Mejia (@brittny_mejia) February 26, 2017 #Trump supporters chanting USA and "Americans first." pic.twitter.com/I13wdNouda 
— Brittny Mejia (@brittny_mejia) February 26, 2017 "Hollywood, don't divide us," #Trump supporters chant. pic.twitter.com/MVvlX8whDk 
— Brittny Mejia (@brittny_mejia) February 26, 2017 Little background on the gathering out here. About a dozen #Trump supporters here. pic.twitter.com/e3tHwV6c9Y 
— Brittny Mejia (@brittny_mejia) February 26, 2017 Newest chant out here by #Trump supporters: "Celebrities don't speak for us." 
— Brittny Mejia (@brittny_mejia) February 26, 2017 Small crowd of #Trump supporters gathered outside Metro station in Hollywood. Some tense encounters already pic.twitter.com/Si3dAJw4C6 
— Brittny Mejia (@brittny_mejia) February 26, 2017 Trending
